                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2028.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Saltillo</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Saltillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-27T13:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 27, 1911—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Yesterday the State leader of Coahuila elected Oscar Garza, a banker, provisional
                    governor, but Madero insisted upon election of Carranza, who was chosen this
                    morning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Voetter.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
